</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/lqg8Lqz</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[springelmogizmo]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Finally got me</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/uB8xdU4</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/4bEAknE.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Fully vaxxed by May 2021, boosted in December of 2021, wear my mask everywhere, limit contact (didn't even go see Spoderman and wanted to soooo badly), aaaaand that ol bitch rona still got me.

Avoided this thing since it all started.  Have no idea where I got it.  Work has strict protocols.  Maybe the kiddo carried it from school?  A grocery store visit?  Idk. 

First day of symptoms I was tired and had a runny nose.  
Day two was shit. Eff that day.  Boddy aches, sinuses on fire, runny nose, super tired, body aches, coughing, did I mention body aches, and no fever.
Day (today) three body aches are almost nonexistent, nose congestion better, nose not as runny, cough already improved, and still no fever.

I'm certain the vaccine is doing its job just based on how other illnesses I've had go.  I never start to feel better as soon as I am now. 

Could be anecdotal.  Idk.

